name: Ca2+/calmodulin-dependent protein kinase
reaction: ATP + a protein = ADP + a phosphoprotein [RN:R00162]
comment: Requires calmodulin and Ca2+ for activity. A wide range of proteins can act as acceptor, including vimentin, synapsin, glycogen synthase, myosin light chains and the microtubule-associated tau protein. Not identical with EC 2.7.11.18 (myosin-light-chain kinase) or EC 2.7.11.26 (tau-protein kinase).

orthologs.K08795: pregnancy upregulated non-ubiquitously expressed CaM kinase
